  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "There does not appear to be a straight forward way to get Ether send \"txs\" from a contract.  For example the contract http://etherscan.io/address/0xde0b295669a9fd93d5f28d9ec85e40f4cb697bae has disbursed ETH payments but tracking the outgoing disbursements are tricky.\n\nThere are also similar request for this functionality https://www.reddit.com/r/ethereum/comments/3ih313/understanding_payments_sent_by_invoked_contracts/\n\nWould be helpful if perhaps https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/JSON-RPC#eth_gettransactionreceipt could be expanded to also include an array of transactions/calls from the contract. For example\nfrom, to, value in a contractTx array\n",
